div.p: The researcher sends computation requests to the server and retrieves the results.
div.div: The Docker image container contains the code (computation) that the nodes should execute.
Researchers can use predefined Docker images or upload their own to the registry.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(17, 179, 232); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 160px; max-width: 252px; width: 252px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.p: The central server handles authentication, keeps track of all computation requests, assigns them to nodes and stores the results of the computation requests.
This server also hosts a Docker registry

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(17, 179, 232); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 242px; max-width: 291px; width: 291px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.p: A node has access to its site's data. It listens (websockets) for work (computation requests).
Once it receives a request, it executes the request by:

ul.li: running the image with the input parameters

div.div: The code that runs in the image has access to the local data through the node.
The results should never contain any identifiable (patient) information, but only aggregated statistics.
